	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 29th 1:20 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Couple questions involving rogues and such:&nbsp;&nbsp;First of all, circle straifing, can it work on melee mobs or just casters?  Is there a good way to set up backstab (as a key) so I can do this manuver fast, right now I'm using the mouse, the number keys on the right and backstab is on the other side of the board (the 2 key).  Any tips on this would be appreciated. <br><br>Skills, emerald dagger favored strength as the main rogue skill, EQlizer encouraged agility others stressed the importance of dexterity.  Any opinions on what abilities are most important?<br><br>Dual wield, can a weapon skill improve on the secondary hand or only in the primary?  Been playing a Paladin so dual wield is a new experience. <br><br>And what are some good weapons one can get at low levels besides piercing?  Do any high level rogues use a 1h blunt?<br> <br>Thats about it for now, got two weeks of playing a rogue under my belt and there's a few things I know for sure:<br><br>1. Backstab is sweeet, few things on eq are funner than stabbing a fleeing goblin, gnoll, x-wife (jk) in the back.  <br><br>2.  IT'S A KILT! not a skirt on Barbs, call it a skirt and I'll rip your lungs out. <br><br>3. When you hear the shout &quot;train!&quot; click hide, sneak and enjoy the show.  <br><br>4. I'll never understand how a 7ft Barb can hide in the middle of the plains of Karana. *Look I'm a tree.*<br><br>Tangus, lv 13 rogue Barb<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
